Week 6 roundup: Around Northeast Florida high school football 
Sat, Oct 3, 2015 @ 12:18 am 
ELSEWHERE 
Jadarius Byrd had a pair of interceptions and White (2-4, 1-1 District 4-6A) stormed back from a first-quarter deficit to defeat Middleburg 35-14. The Broncos fell to 0-6, 0-2. ... Fernandina Beach (2-4, 1-1 District 2-4A) snapped a long losing skid in district play with a 24-12 win over visiting Jackson (0-5, 0-2). ... Christâ€™s Church (5-1) suffered its first loss to Lake Mary Prep (1-3), falling 22-14. ... Bishop Snyder (2-4) saw its losing streak grow to four games in a 7-6 loss at Interlachen (1-4). ... Sadarious Carter intercepted a pass in the end zone as time expired, sending the Red Flashes to a District 6-1A loss to Hawthorne (5-1, 2-0)... Hilliard (2-3, 0-2) drove to the 5-yard line with six seconds to play, but Carter picked off the fourth-down pass.
